Global Hydro Turbines Market Insights
Hydro Turbines Market size was valued at USD 4.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 6.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Hydro Turbines Market Overview
The global hydro turbine market was valued at approximately USD 2.77 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach around USD 3.91 billion by 2034, expanding at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 3.50% during the forecast period. The Asia-Pacific region holds the largest market share, accounting for about 39% in 2023, and is expected to continue its dominance due to significant investments in hydropower infrastructure. Europe is anticipated to experience the fastest growth, driven by supportive government policies and a strong emphasis on renewable energy sources. The impulse turbine segment led the market with a 63% revenue share in 2023, while the reaction turbine segment is expected to grow at a notable CAGR of 5.8% during the forecast period. The low head turbine segment recorded more than 42% of revenue share in 2023, with the high head turbine segment estimated to expand at the fastest CAGR over the projected period. The small hydro power plant segment registered the maximum market share of 36.8% in 2023, with the large hydropower plant segment predicted to grow at a remarkable CAGR over the projected period.

